strumentation/opentelemetry-spring-boot-autoconfigure/2.28.1/src/test/java/io_opentelemetry_instrumentation/opentelemetry_spring_boot_autoconfigure/Opentelemetry_spring_boot_autoconfigureTest.java`\n\nWhat was already covered:\n- Spring Boot auto-configuration creates a configured OpenTelemetry SDK bean.\n- Trace context propagation works through an auto-instrumented `RestTemplate`.\n- `otel.sdk.disabled=true` provides a noop `OpenTelemetry` bean.\n\nNew coverage added:\n- Verifies Spring Boot auto-configuration instruments the public Spring `RestClient.Builder` API.\n- Builds a `RestClient` from the auto-configured builder.\n- Uses `MockRestServiceServer` to assert outgoing requests include a `traceparent` header.\n- Keeps bounded verification with a 10-second timeout.\n\nNo build files or existing test logic were changed. I did not run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_020e8a48e9399692016a3e905331888197b3c36e6a2acf6b5a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1696, "output": 406, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37942, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782485068475, "responseId": "resp_020e8a48e9399692016a3e904daddc81978cbca9a55b0968e0"}}
